    <p><b>Information we collect about you:</b></p>

    <p><br />
    </p>

    <ol > <li>We collect information that you voluntarily provide in order to become a registered user of our Services, and when you update your profile in the course of using the Services. (For example, we collect your name, email address, location information, and various other background information this way.)</li>
    </ol><p><br />
    </p>

    <ol > <li>You may join the Services by logging in to your Facebook account; and you may establish linkages between your account at The Shoplift and your accounts at Facebook, Twitter, and/or Pinterest (collectively, “Other Social Networks”). When you do so we may collect certain publicly accessible information about you. (For instance, we may collect your name and profile photo.) </li>
    </ol><p><br />
    </p>

    <p>We may also collect nonpublic information about you, as permitted by the privacy settings you have established on the Other Social Networks to which you allow access. This information generally helps us create a more social environment. (For example, knowing who your Facebook friends are allows us to help you find and follow them at The Shoplift.) </p>

    <p><br />
    </p>

    <p>In short, you should assume that we are collecting any information about you permitted by the privacy settings you establish on Other Social Networks. Please consult the privacy policies of, and check your personal privacy settings on, Facebook, Twitter, and Pinterest before allowing us to access your accounts at these platforms.</p>

    <p><br />
    </p>

    <ol > <li>We collect other information that you voluntarily provide in the course of using the Services, such as when you enter an email address on a form to send an email from your account at The Shoplift. </li>
    </ol><p><br />
    </p>

    <ol > <li>We collect information associated with User Content you Post. This includes information we collect from third-party websites (such as item images, brands, item names, and prices), information you contribute manually (such as comments and tags), and the record of various usage decisions you make (such as the decision to follow or unfollow other users, or the decision to save or unsave a particular item). </li>
    </ol><p><br />
    </p>

    <ol > <li>Our servers automatically record certain information (“Log Data”) that your web browser and/or mobile application sends when you use the Services. Log Data may include, without limitation, information about your device and software (such as browser type, IP address, referring domain, mobile device type, operating system, software version, geographic location, and mobile carrier) and information about your navigation and activity within the Services (such as pages visited, items viewed, navigation path taken, and certain timing information). We may also employ one or more cookies that may uniquely identify your web browser. These cookies may or may not be deleted from your computer when you log off from the Services or close your browser. You should customize your browser settings to meet your personal privacy preferences regarding the use of cookies. </li>
    </ol><p><br />
    </p>

    <p>Across all five of these categories of information we collect, the information we collect includes information that can be used to identify or contact you (“Personal Information”). We collect other, non-identifying information as well; but we may sometimes collect non-identifying information in combination with Personal Information, or store, use, or share the two kinds of information together, in a way that enables you to be personally identified or contacted. </p>

